Dataset:-

For this project, we used the Fake and Real News Dataset from Kaggle.

How to Access the Dataset:

Visit the Dataset Page: Go to Fake and Real News Dataset on Kaggle [https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/clmentbisaillon/fake-and-real-news-dataset].

#Download the Dataset:-

If you donâ€™t have a Kaggle account, you will need to create one.

Once logged in, click the "Download" button on the dataset page to get the data.

Extract the Files: The downloaded file will be in a zip format. Extract it to get the CSV files containing the news articles.

#Using the Dataset:-

Place the Dataset: Move the extracted CSV files into the data directory of this project.

Preprocess the Data: Run the preprocessing script provided in the repository to clean and prepare the data for training.

Train and Test: Use the provided scripts to train the machine learning models on the dataset and test their performance.
